<TITLE> Stocks open down, led by banks </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 27 (bdnews24.com)  Dhaka stocks opened down on Thursday amid banks' continued domination on the turnover board. The market saw a steep fall at the opening but immediately recovered losses before declining again in the midday sessions. At 12.33 pm, the DGEN or general index fell 29.93 points or 0.98 percent at 2998.73. The DSI or all share price index was at 2518.23, down 28.47 points or 1.11 percent. Turnover stood at Tk 733.67 million from trading of 2,113,955 shares. Losers outnumbered gainers 114 to 62 and some 14 issues held steady. UCBL remained at the top of the share value board, though it was selling down at Tk 3850 from the previous day's closing of Tk 4453.75. Market major Square Pharma followed UCBL, selling high at Tk 3522 from Tk 3486 the previous day. Prime Bank fell after gaining the previous day. It was selling at Tk 915 from Tk 931. Uttara Bank also declined to Tk 4829 from Wednesday's Tk 4881.75. BRAC Bank continued its decline from the previous day, selling at Tk 1610 from Tk 1628.25. Power sector heavyweight Power Grid Company of Bangladesh also fell. The company has announced that an EGM of the company will be held on Dec 31 to amend some clauses of the Articles of Association of the Company. Among the other scrips on the top share values board  Shahjalal Bank, Islami Bank Perpetual Bond and NBL declined. Heidelberg Cement however rose. bdn
